        "title": "The Raid",
        "body": "The operation spanned states from Tamil Nadu to West Bengal, with simultaneous searches conducted in urban centres and smaller towns. The CBI arrested B. Naresh from Chennai and Sanjib Saha from Kolkata, both accused of operating shell companies and maintaining a network of mule bank accounts used to launder approximately Rs 2 crore in scam proceeds. Investigators seized digital devices, incriminating documents, and evidence linking the accused to a larger syndicate that may have defrauded victims across multiple jurisdictions. The scale of the operation â€” 80-plus locations, 60 teams, 16 states â€” reflects the depth and geographical spread of the scam network, which the CBI believes has been active for several years."
