        "body": "The scam followed a chillingly effective script. Victims would receive calls or video calls from individuals impersonating police officers, CBI officials, or judicial officers. The caller would allege involvement in a serious crime â€” money laundering, drug trafficking, or terrorism â€” and inform the victim that a warrant had been issued for their arrest. To lend credibility, the fraudsters directed victims to the fake Supreme Court website, where the fabricated charges and forged warrants could be viewed. The victim was then placed under \"digital arrest\" â€” confined to their home and required to remain on a video call for hours or days â€” while being coerced into transferring money to designated accounts to secure bail or avoid prosecution. The psychological manipulation was extreme: victims were isolated, threatened, and prevented from contacting family members or legal counsel."
