        "body": "Evidence gathered during the raids suggests that the scam network may have targeted foreign nationals as well, expanding its victim pool beyond India. The CBI has alerted overseas law enforcement agencies through Interpol channels, sharing intelligence on the modus operandi, the domain registration patterns, and the money trail. The international dimension adds significant complexity to the investigation, requiring coordination with multiple foreign jurisdictions. Operation Chakra-VI builds on previous phases: Chakra I-III targeted fraudulent call centres, while Chakra IV-V focused on illegal payment gateways and mule accounts. The CBI has indicated that further arrests are expected as forensic analysis of seized devices continues, and that Operation Chakra-VII is already in the planning stages."
