        "body": "On June 22, 2026, Tata Electronics — a critical supplier to both Apple and Tesla — confirmed it had been hit by a devastating ransomware attack. The group behind it, World Leaks, claims to have stolen 204,300 files totalling 630 gigabytes of data. Among the alleged haul are Apple's proprietary iPhone circuit board inspection standards, Tesla's engineering drawings marked \"TRADE SECRET\" for the Model 3 revamp, employee passport scans, internal emails, and SAP records. The files have been on the dark web since at least June 10. Tata confirmed the breach twelve days later. Apple is investigating. Tesla has said nothing. India's ambition to become an electronics manufacturing superpower just hit its most serious credibility test yet."
