        "body": "World Leaks emerged in January 2025 as a rebrand of Hunters International, which inherited tactics from the Hive ransomware operation dismantled by the FBI in 2023. Unlike traditional ransomware groups that encrypt files, World Leaks operates an Extortion-as-a-Service platform. Affiliates steal data using custom tools and publish it on a dark web leak site unless the victim pays. No encryption required — just theft and the threat of exposure. The group's known initial access vector is compromised VPN credentials lacking multi-factor authentication, the kind of vulnerability that proliferates in companies that prioritise production over security. World Leaks has claimed 125 victims globally, with the United States and India as primary targets. Previous victims include Dell Technologies (1.3 terabytes stolen in 2025) and Nike."
